AngloGold Says Tanzanian Mining Agreement Remains in Place

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-10-20T09:34:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/anglogold-says-tanzanian-mining-agreement-remains-in-place.html
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG) , the world’s
third-largest mining company, said its Mining Development
Agreement in Tanzania remains in place “from our perspective.”  AngloGold commented on Tanzania’s plan to raise the royalty
rate applicable to gold and other metal producers to 4 percent
from 3 percent. The Johannesburg-based company commented in an
e-mail today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carli Lourens at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net  